  {
    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Gill's Exposition of the Entire Bible",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "The Lord shall cause thine enemies that rise up against thee to be smitten before thy face,.... As the Philistines, Moabites, Syrians, Edomites, and Ammonites were, especially in the times of David: ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "they shall come out against thee one way: in a body, all together, in large numbers, marching in great order, to give them battle: ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "and flee before thee seven ways; be entirely routed, and flee some one way, and some another, even every way they could take to make their escape. The phrase is expressive of an entire victory, and of a complete rout and dispersion of an enemy. ",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "and flee before thee seven ways; be entirely routed, and flee some one way, and some another, even every way they could take to make their escape. The phrase is expressive of an entire victory, and of a complete rout and dispersion of an enemy. ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
